						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine, Bhaktajanēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 3: 974 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that twenty-four <hi rend="italic">śeṟuvu</hi> of land (spreading) in four territorial divisions <hi rend="italic">(sīmai)</hi> donated by Iruṇīkki Aḍaiyakkōṉ to the deity Tiruttoṇḍīśvaratt-āḻvār, is set-apart for maintaining five persons, cleaning the floors and walls of the temple. </p>						

